Health & Fitness Analytics Project

Project Objective

The objective of this project is to analyze how different training regimens, diet quality, and rest periods affect athletic performance and injury risk.

Summary and Recommendations

The analysis indicates that Rest Hours and Age are the most important factors in predicting performance. However, high training intensity and poor rest lead to higher injury risk, as shown by the logistic regression analysis.

Recommendations:

  • Focus on improving rest and recovery strategies to enhance performance while reducing injury risk.
  • Custom training programs based on athlete age and fitness level to optimize performance.
  • Implement targeted interventions for high-risk athletes identified through PCA and feature importance analysis.
